Step 2/3
2. Next, we need to estimate the birth rate in Indonesia in 2026. According to the United Nations Population Division, the total fertility rate (TFR) in Indonesia in 2021 was 2.26 children per woman. Assuming that the TFR remains constant, we can estimate the birth rate in 2026 by multiplying the TFR by the total population in 2026.

Step 3/3
3. To estimate the total population in 2026, we can use the United Nations' population projections for Indonesia. According to these projections, the population of Indonesia in 2026 is expected to be 277.3 million. 2 of 4

The population density is the number of people per square kilometer.

3 of 4

The energy consumption in 2027 will be:

$\begin{aligned} \text{Energy consumption in 2027}&=\text{Population density in 2027}\cdot\text{Energy consumption in 2012}\\ &=4.3\cdot1.4\\ &=6.02\text{ quadrillion BTU} \end{aligned}$
